# Copy to .env and point at whichever OpenAI-compatible backend you're using.
# Leave LLM_BASE_URL blank to run WITHOUT AI (rule-based, uses victim's own fields).
# The command post speaks plain OpenAI /v1/chat/completions, so switching backend is
# ONE line here — no code change.

# --- AI PC (Snapdragon X Elite) — GenieX on the Hexagon NPU (see setup-geniex.ps1) ---
# `geniex serve` exposes an OpenAI API at 127.0.0.1:18181/v1. LLM_MODEL must be the id
# GenieX serves (whatever you `geniex pull`ed). Default = heretic 8B @ Q4_0 on the NPU.
# An 8B's first call includes model load, so give it a longer timeout.
# LLM_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:18181/v1
# LLM_MODEL=bartowski/p-e-w_Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct-heretic-GGUF
# LLM_TIMEOUT_S=60

# --- Second model: fast structured tag extraction (triage.extract_tags) ---
# A SEPARATE geniex serve on another port running the small Gemma 4 E2B, kept resident
# ALONGSIDE the E4B triage model above. Two servers keep BOTH models warm on the NPU (~1 s
# each); a single server reloads ~15 s on every model switch. dev.ps1 starts both. If left
# unset, tag extraction falls back to the LLM_* backend above (single-model, slower).
# TAGS_LLM_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:18182/v1
# TAGS_LLM_MODEL=bartowski/google_gemma-4-E2B-it-GGUF:Q4_K_M

# --- Dev / fallbacks (all OpenAI-compatible) ---
# Ollama:  http://localhost:11434/v1   (then `ollama pull llama3.2:3b`)
# LM Studio (Mac/MLX): http://localhost:1234/v1   |   vLLM: :8000/v1   |   llama.cpp: :8080/v1
LLM_BASE_URL=
LLM_MODEL=llama3.2:3b
LLM_API_KEY=not-needed
LLM_TIMEOUT_S=20

# Each backend start creates a new blank session; PostgreSQL retains prior sessions.
# Run ./setup-postgres.sh to generate real local credentials (never commit them).
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://sankat:replace-me@127.0.0.1:55432/sankat_mochan
SANKAT_DATABASE_REQUIRED=true
